- **WORKAROUND [2026-03-29]: browser drag-drop upload blocked by security restrictions** — UI-level file upload blocked. Fix: used Kling File Upload API endpoint directly with `curl`. Signals general pattern: when browser-based upload blocked, switch to direct API endpoint. <!-- decay:2026-03-29 tier:cold rel:0.565 -->

### Cross-Project Patterns

- **ENHANCEMENT: Centralize config in shared/ modules** — store paths, credentials refs, and constants in `shared/` modules; import once, use everywhere. Reduces duplication and enables atomic updates across multiple dependents. <!-- decay:2026-03-29 tier:cold rel:0.565 -->
- **PATTERN: Verify stale data via file modification times** — use `stat` command and compare timestamps against last known good state. Delete orphaned files explicitly rather than leaving them. <!-- decay:2026-03-29 tier:cold rel:0.565 -->
- **PATTERN: Run smoke tests after architecture changes** — verify JSON syntax, import resolution, and dependent module execution after any structural refactor. Catches integration failures early. <!-- decay:2026-03-29 tier:cold rel:0.565 -->
- **ENHANCEMENT: Use deny_patterns as security barrier** — maintain an allowlist of dangerous command patterns (`curl|bash`, `chmod 777`, etc.) in `settings.json`. Update constitution when new risk patterns emerge. <!-- decay:2026-03-29 tier:cold rel:0.565 -->

