## Distilled 2026-04-25 (from global-patterns)

### Debugging & Conflict Resolution

- **PATTERN: Identify all report sources** — when fixing data consistency issues, identify ALL sources generating those reports (e.g., vault-audit for stdout, generate-moc.js for static markdown) and apply consistent logic to each.
- **PATTERN: Audit existing configs for conflicts** — when debugging unexpected WP behavior, audit existing code snippets and mu-plugins to identify conflicting sources (e.g., Product Schema from post_meta vs. Yoast).
- **PATTERN: When plan contradicts live system** — audit live system to understand actual state, update plan to reflect reality before proceeding. Priority: actual state over documentation.
- **PATTERN: mu-plugin for centralized WP changes** — for WP changes affecting SEO/Schema, use mu-plugin for centralized management and easy deploy.
